The paper proposes a hybrid model for multivariate time series forecasting that combines linear models (like VAR) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs). This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and time series analysis. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new machine learning model for time series forecasting, which combines linear models and RNNs. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new AI model for time series forecasting, which combines linear models and RNNs. 

cs.ST (Statistics): The paper deals with time series analysis and forecasting, which is a topic of interest in statistics. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new neural network model for time series forecasting, which combines linear models and RNNs. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with time series data from the aviation and climate domains, which could be considered as social and information networks.
